main event: The report describes the sighting of a bright, metallic object in the sky at around 10:55 PM on September 2, 1964 in the area between Silver Spring and Riverdale, Maryland.
interesting points: The object was described as being around the size of a large star, with a bright glow around the edges.
The object was silent and the witness had a better view of the object than the person who initially spotted it.
The witness had seen UFOs before and had more experience with such sightings.
The object was visible for about 10-15 seconds.
The report mentions that AP 117 was sent to Mr. [redacted] on 18 Sept 1968.
sighted object: a bright, metallic object in the sky
location: Between Silver Spring and Riverdale, Maryland
